(1) Hiring rates are calculated using the total count of employee hires for the financial year as the numerator and total number of employees averaged across the financial year as the denominator.

(1) Turnover rates are calculated using the total count of applicable employee exits for the financial year as the numerator and the total number of employees averaged across the financial year as the denominator. The numerator includes employee exits that were voluntary or due to dismissal, retirement or death in service. These figures exclude employee departures as a result of redundancy or end of contract.\n

(5) A primary caregiver is the parent who assumes the principal role for having primary responsibilities for providing care and support to the child following the birth of the child.
(6) A secondary caregiver is the legally recognised partner, spouse or de facto spouse of the primary caregiver, who does not have primary caregiving responsibilities for the child.
